1
00:00:03,108 --> 00:00:08,989
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL - BAUDELAIRE

2
00:00:09,072 --> 00:00:10,073
MIYAMA BOOKSTORE

3
00:00:10,157 --> 00:00:11,783
[Takao] Dear Baudelaire,

4
00:00:12,284 --> 00:00:14,119
can you believe this?

5
00:00:14,870 --> 00:00:16,580
For the first time in my life,

6
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:18,915
I'm witnessing with my own eyes,

7
00:00:18,999 --> 00:00:20,792
someone reading that book!

8
00:00:25,964 --> 00:00:27,174
Tokiwa,

9
00:00:27,674 --> 00:00:28,759
that book...

10
00:00:29,885 --> 00:00:32,054
The Flowers of Evil... Why are you...?

11
00:00:32,137 --> 00:00:33,513
What's your problem?

12
00:00:33,597 --> 00:00:35,557
You're creeping me out.

13
00:00:35,641 --> 00:00:39,061
It's just... That book...

14
00:00:39,603 --> 00:00:41,897
I've never seen anyone reading it.

15
00:00:43,190 --> 00:00:44,691
Sorry.

16
00:00:45,442 --> 00:00:46,693
[Aya] Hey, wait a minute!

17
00:00:49,821 --> 00:00:50,822
SANITIZING WIPES

18
00:00:50,906 --> 00:00:52,157
Do you want one?

19
00:00:53,617 --> 00:00:55,869
Yeah, thanks.

20
00:01:00,082 --> 00:01:01,583
I'm surprised you know it.

21
00:01:01,666 --> 00:01:03,335
It's a pretty obscure book.

22
00:01:04,836 --> 00:01:06,296
When I was in junior high,

23
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:08,840
I read it till the pages wore out.

24
00:01:09,675 --> 00:01:11,426
[chuckles softly] Impressive.

25
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:13,929
Actually,

26
00:01:14,012 --> 00:01:15,972
a mystery novel I read recently

27
00:01:16,056 --> 00:01:18,475
used one of his poems to solve the trick.

28
00:01:18,975 --> 00:01:22,145
So, when I saw it on the shelf here,
I thought I'd take a look.

29
00:01:22,229 --> 00:01:24,189
Honestly, I don't really get it.

30
00:01:29,403 --> 00:01:32,114
You like books?

31
00:01:33,448 --> 00:01:34,658
I do...

32
00:01:35,659 --> 00:01:36,702
I mean, I did.

33
00:01:38,745 --> 00:01:40,539
I don't read at all now.

34
00:01:41,331 --> 00:01:42,332
Why not?

35
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:43,875
Busy with club activities?

36
00:01:44,459 --> 00:01:45,585
[Takao] Well, no...

37
00:01:48,130 --> 00:01:49,214
Do you wanna read it?

38
00:01:50,424 --> 00:01:52,175
The mystery novel I mentioned.

39
00:01:53,301 --> 00:01:54,761
I just finished it.

40
00:02:20,454 --> 00:02:22,080
[sighs]

41
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:30,172
[♪ gentle music playing]

42
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:57,115
[♪ opening theme music playing]

43
00:03:52,754 --> 00:03:55,006
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

44
00:03:55,090 --> 00:03:56,341
[Takao] Thanks for this.

45
00:03:56,466 --> 00:03:57,676
[Aya] You finished it already?

46
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:58,760
EPISODE 9

47
00:03:58,843 --> 00:04:00,804
It was a really good book!

48
00:04:00,887 --> 00:04:03,890
I kept wondering what comes next.
I couldn't put it down.

49
00:04:04,391 --> 00:04:05,475
Right?

50
00:04:05,559 --> 00:04:08,270
There's a sequel, isn't there?

51
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:11,523
[chuckles]

52
00:04:14,776 --> 00:04:16,486
[exclaims]

53
00:04:18,363 --> 00:04:19,406
Here.

54
00:04:19,489 --> 00:04:21,783
No way! Thank you.

55
00:04:22,659 --> 00:04:25,161
I kept wondering what happens
to the protagonist.

56
00:04:25,245 --> 00:04:29,666
To be honest, I couldn't concentrate
on my studies or anything.
STYLE
::cue()

57
00:04:29,749 --> 00:04:31,126
[laughing]

58
00:04:31,209 --> 00:04:33,211
[laughter echoes]

59
00:04:36,464 --> 00:04:37,883
I know, right?

60
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:41,094
Hey, let me borrow one of your books, too.

61
00:04:41,553 --> 00:04:42,721
Ah.

62
00:04:42,804 --> 00:04:44,890
Nothing like The Flowers of Evil, please.

63
00:04:45,557 --> 00:04:49,394
Got anything more serious,
with substance, and fun to read?

64
00:04:50,896 --> 00:04:54,274
I got rid of all my books
when we moved here.

65
00:04:54,774 --> 00:04:56,484
Just give me the titles, then.

66
00:04:56,568 --> 00:04:58,278
You used to read a lot, right?

67
00:05:05,619 --> 00:05:06,661
Takao!

68
00:05:07,162 --> 00:05:09,289
How you doin' these days? Everything good?

69
00:05:09,789 --> 00:05:10,957
Now, listen.

70
00:05:11,458 --> 00:05:14,002
Don't worry your mother, you understand?

71
00:05:14,085 --> 00:05:17,297
Hey! Go take a bath already!

72
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:19,424
-What'd you say?!
-[Shizue groans]

73
00:05:19,507 --> 00:05:21,259
Don't nag me like that.

74
00:05:21,343 --> 00:05:23,637
I've been working all day, you know.

75
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:26,139
[Shizue] And I do the housework
on top of a part-time job.

76
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,142
[Tetsuo] Well,
I'm sorry I get paid peanuts.

77
00:05:29,225 --> 00:05:31,478
Do you think I want to be in this job?!

78
00:05:31,561 --> 00:05:34,147
[Shizue] Here we go again...

79
00:05:34,230 --> 00:05:35,231
What's that?!

80
00:05:35,315 --> 00:05:36,733
[indistinct chatter]

81
00:05:39,611 --> 00:05:40,612
[Takao] Here.

82
00:05:41,488 --> 00:05:44,240
-[Aya] Wow.
-[♪ pleasant music playing]

83
00:05:44,324 --> 00:05:49,412
Tsutsui? I like his work, too.
You like Erotic Avenue?

84
00:05:49,496 --> 00:05:53,083
I liked
Lagos on a Journey better. [chuckles]

85
00:05:53,166 --> 00:05:55,502
[chuckles awkwardly] Sorry.

86
00:05:56,503 --> 00:05:57,504
What?

87
00:05:58,129 --> 00:06:01,007
Why are you apologizing? [laughing]

88
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,134
You're silly.

89
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:12,644
[grunts]

90
00:06:15,438 --> 00:06:16,898
[Takao] Thanks for lending it to me.

91
00:06:17,565 --> 00:06:19,275
It was really interesting.

92
00:06:19,359 --> 00:06:21,528
[Aya exclaims] This is from me, then.

93
00:06:21,611 --> 00:06:22,612
Here.

94
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:25,156
-I told you it's not.
-[chuckles]

95
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,574
Is that Kasuga over there?

96
00:06:26,658 --> 00:06:28,576
-[Tamaru] What?
-What's he doing?

97
00:06:29,119 --> 00:06:30,161
[Tamaru] He's reading a book.

98
00:06:30,245 --> 00:06:32,414
[Sasaki] That's not like him.

99
00:06:34,958 --> 00:06:37,752
THE METAMORPHOSIS X KAFKA
TRANSLATION BY YOSHITAKA TAKAHASHI

100
00:06:40,588 --> 00:06:42,507
[Aya] I read it, but,

101
00:06:42,590 --> 00:06:45,051
you sure have terrible taste!

102
00:06:45,135 --> 00:06:47,178
[chuckles awkwardly] Sorry about that.

103
00:06:47,262 --> 00:06:50,724
That unsettling feeling that
maybe people are really like this.

104
00:06:50,807 --> 00:06:56,688
Right... I see your point.
You... think so?

105
00:06:56,771 --> 00:07:00,358
Come on! You're the one
who recommended it to me!

106
00:07:01,109 --> 00:07:03,903
You have to get it together!

107
00:07:03,987 --> 00:07:07,031
You're the only one
I can talk to about books.

108
00:07:09,075 --> 00:07:10,201
Sorry.

109
00:07:11,244 --> 00:07:13,037
[laughter echoes]

110
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:20,211
Kasuga, we saw you yesterday.
Getting some alone time with Tokiwa.

111
00:07:20,712 --> 00:07:23,757
No, that's not...
I was just borrowing a book from her.

112
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:26,134
Too bad, Kasuga.

113
00:07:26,217 --> 00:07:28,011
Tokiwa has a boyfriend!

114
00:07:28,094 --> 00:07:32,223
I heard he's a third year at North High,
and they met at her part-time job!

115
00:07:32,307 --> 00:07:34,934
What a fleeting romance
it was for you, Kasuga.

116
00:07:35,018 --> 00:07:37,520
We won't let you get ahead of us.
Right, guys?

117
00:07:37,604 --> 00:07:41,232
-[boys laughing]
-Come on, it's not like that.

118
00:07:41,316 --> 00:07:43,151
[boys] Mmm.

119
00:07:43,234 --> 00:07:46,237
[Takao] What are you doing,
trying to build relationships with people?

120
00:07:46,988 --> 00:07:49,491
Have you forgotten what you did?

121
00:07:50,116 --> 00:07:51,367
You shit bug!

122
00:07:52,994 --> 00:07:53,995
Hey ya.

123
00:07:57,707 --> 00:07:59,417
Thanks for letting me borrow these.

124
00:07:59,501 --> 00:08:00,960
Weren't they great?

125
00:08:01,044 --> 00:08:03,379
I think they're the best
of the whole series.

126
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:04,881
Yeah.

127
00:08:06,174 --> 00:08:08,384
What? You didn't care for them?

128
00:08:08,468 --> 00:08:11,805
That's not it at all!
I can't wait to read the rest.

129
00:08:13,306 --> 00:08:14,641
I'm sorry.

130
00:08:14,724 --> 00:08:18,436
I stayed at a friends' house last night,
so I don't have the next volume.

131
00:08:19,979 --> 00:08:21,397
Your friends' house...

132
00:08:22,524 --> 00:08:23,608
Of course.

133
00:08:23,691 --> 00:08:27,529
[laughing] Wait, what is this?
Are you that bummed about it?

134
00:08:28,822 --> 00:08:31,491
Wanna come over to my house to get it?

135
00:08:32,075 --> 00:08:33,076
What?!

136
00:08:33,576 --> 00:08:34,953
[Kanami] There you are!

137
00:08:35,036 --> 00:08:36,788
Tokiwa!

138
00:08:38,915 --> 00:08:40,792
Why don't you come to this with us?

139
00:08:40,875 --> 00:08:42,627
[Aya] Sorry, I have plans today.

140
00:08:42,710 --> 00:08:45,463
Okay, then. We'll see you tomorrow.

141
00:08:45,547 --> 00:08:46,631
-Yeah.
-See you.

142
00:08:46,714 --> 00:08:48,424
-Bye.
-Bye-bye.

143
00:08:49,092 --> 00:08:50,426
Who was that next to her?

144
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:53,304
-[Yuki] No clue.
-[Kanami] Off we go, off we go.

145
00:08:53,388 --> 00:08:54,639
[Aya] Let's go.

146
00:08:54,722 --> 00:08:56,099
Okay, sure.
STYLE
::cue()

147
00:08:56,182 --> 00:08:59,060
TOKIWA

148
00:09:02,021 --> 00:09:03,648
[Aya] You can relax, you know.

149
00:09:04,274 --> 00:09:08,444
Well, I mean...
I'll leave as soon as I borrow the book.

150
00:09:08,945 --> 00:09:11,489
[Aya] Where did I put that one...

151
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:16,327
What?

152
00:09:17,871 --> 00:09:19,080
This is amazing!

153
00:09:21,166 --> 00:09:24,210
Hey, don't gawk at it like that.

154
00:09:24,294 --> 00:09:28,214
[Takao] I don't mean to, but...
You've read all of these books, right?

155
00:09:28,298 --> 00:09:30,717
You must really love to read.

156
00:09:31,801 --> 00:09:32,927
It really is amazing.

157
00:09:33,011 --> 00:09:35,180
Stop it already. [chuckles]

158
00:09:37,807 --> 00:09:40,268
PLOT

159
00:09:47,734 --> 00:09:48,818
[gasps]

160
00:09:48,902 --> 00:09:50,737
[♪ gentle music playing]

161
00:09:52,071 --> 00:09:53,907
What is that?

162
00:09:54,657 --> 00:09:57,035
It's nothing.

163
00:09:58,077 --> 00:09:59,162
By any chance...

164
00:09:59,662 --> 00:10:01,706
Is it a novel you wrote?

165
00:10:01,789 --> 00:10:02,832
No, it isn't.

166
00:10:05,043 --> 00:10:06,252
Can't I take a peek?

167
00:10:06,336 --> 00:10:08,213
I'm telling you it's not!

168
00:10:25,188 --> 00:10:26,564
[phone vibrating]

169
00:10:32,862 --> 00:10:34,113
Hello?

170
00:10:35,573 --> 00:10:38,201
What? Wait a second, it's nothing like--

171
00:10:38,993 --> 00:10:39,994
What?

172
00:10:47,835 --> 00:10:49,045
Kasuga,

173
00:10:49,796 --> 00:10:50,797
I'm sorry.

174
00:10:51,756 --> 00:10:53,091
My boyfriend's here.

175
00:10:55,426 --> 00:10:56,427
What?

176
00:10:57,387 --> 00:10:59,430
[dog barking]

177
00:11:03,685 --> 00:11:05,353
Thanks for waiting, Koji.

178
00:11:07,981 --> 00:11:09,816
This is Kasuga.

179
00:11:11,484 --> 00:11:12,485
Hello.

180
00:11:15,029 --> 00:11:16,572
[laughing]

181
00:11:16,656 --> 00:11:20,493
No way! I wondered what stud you'd taken
into your room, but this guy?

182
00:11:20,576 --> 00:11:21,953
Well... I'm...

183
00:11:22,537 --> 00:11:24,163
I'm sorry, sir.

184
00:11:24,247 --> 00:11:25,248
[scoffs]

185
00:11:25,331 --> 00:11:28,876
It's obvious you don't have
the guts to do anything.

186
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:31,296
Hey, wanna go to our usual spot?

187
00:11:31,379 --> 00:11:32,922
We can get pizza or something.

188
00:11:33,006 --> 00:11:35,425
Sounds good. Let's go.

189
00:11:37,343 --> 00:11:40,430
[stammers] I'm really, truly sorry.

190
00:11:42,056 --> 00:11:43,391
Hey.

191
00:11:45,101 --> 00:11:48,604
Come with us, Kasuga.

192
00:11:48,688 --> 00:11:49,689
What?

193
00:11:53,109 --> 00:11:55,028
[♪ techno music playing]

194
00:12:02,952 --> 00:12:04,787
Wanna go clubbing? A sick DJ's coming.

195
00:12:04,871 --> 00:12:05,955
-Really?
-For real?

196
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:07,206
We're in!

197
00:12:07,290 --> 00:12:08,291
That's so cool!

198
00:12:08,374 --> 00:12:10,585
[male student 1] We have to go!
Promise, okay?

199
00:12:10,668 --> 00:12:13,629
Hey, you haven't eaten at all.

200
00:12:13,713 --> 00:12:16,174
Go ahead, have some!

201
00:12:16,924 --> 00:12:20,345
-Thank you. I'll take this.
-Sure!

202
00:12:29,812 --> 00:12:33,107
-Dude, you've got cheese right here.
-[all laughing]

203
00:12:33,191 --> 00:12:34,525
-Come on, man.
-Damn.

204
00:12:34,609 --> 00:12:36,194
[female student 1] You're way too nervous.

205
00:12:36,277 --> 00:12:38,363
See? I told you he's funny.

206
00:12:39,072 --> 00:12:41,866
Kasuga, was it? Are you in any clubs?

207
00:12:41,949 --> 00:12:43,910
Wait, wait. I wanna guess.

208
00:12:46,287 --> 00:12:47,288
The Going-Home Club.

209
00:12:48,915 --> 00:12:49,916
That's correct.

210
00:12:49,999 --> 00:12:51,000
[male student 2] I knew it!

211
00:12:51,084 --> 00:12:54,128
Hey, I know.
I bet you're hobby is "reading."

212
00:12:54,212 --> 00:12:55,338
Right?

213
00:12:56,005 --> 00:12:59,258
-[female student 2] Man, you're terrible!
-[all laughing]

214
00:12:59,342 --> 00:13:01,594
How about... a girlfriend?

215
00:13:01,677 --> 00:13:03,429
I bet he doesn't have one!

216
00:13:03,513 --> 00:13:04,847
[female student 3] You're so mean!

217
00:13:04,931 --> 00:13:06,974
So, what's the answer?

218
00:13:08,142 --> 00:13:09,977
-I don't have one.
-[male student 3] Knew it!

219
00:13:10,061 --> 00:13:11,229
So, you're a virgin.

220
00:13:11,312 --> 00:13:13,981
[female student 4] Takuya!
You have no filter!

221
00:13:15,066 --> 00:13:17,360
Do you have a crush on anyone right now?

222
00:13:18,653 --> 00:13:19,654
No,

223
00:13:20,154 --> 00:13:21,155
not in particular.

224
00:13:21,739 --> 00:13:25,743
Come on,
tell us more about yourself, Kasuga!

225
00:13:26,702 --> 00:13:28,830
Okay, then.

226
00:13:28,913 --> 00:13:31,749
The name of your crush from junior high!

227
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,668
[all exclaiming]

228
00:13:33,751 --> 00:13:37,588
Three, two, one, go!

229
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:42,426
[chuckles] Go!
STYLE
::cue()

230
00:13:47,932 --> 00:13:49,392
I don't want to say.

231
00:13:50,685 --> 00:13:53,938
What does it matter, though?
It's in the past.

232
00:13:54,021 --> 00:13:55,231
Cut it out, Koji.

233
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:57,233
All right, then.

234
00:13:57,733 --> 00:14:00,111
How did you get acquainted with Aya?

235
00:14:00,194 --> 00:14:02,780
-We were at karaoke together.
-I didn't ask you, Aya.

236
00:14:02,864 --> 00:14:04,282
Right, Kasuga?

237
00:14:05,199 --> 00:14:06,409
Tell me.

238
00:14:06,492 --> 00:14:09,579
How did things turn out
that you became close with Aya?

239
00:14:10,538 --> 00:14:11,539
Well, I mean...

240
00:14:11,622 --> 00:14:15,501
How did things turn out
that you ended up going to Aya's room?

241
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:17,837
-What? No way.
-Seriously?

242
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:20,339
[Koji] I haven't
stepped foot in there, not once.

243
00:14:20,423 --> 00:14:23,342
No matter how many times I asked,

244
00:14:23,426 --> 00:14:25,720
she'd always say,
"I don't ever let anyone in!"

245
00:14:26,262 --> 00:14:27,346
Isn't that right, Aya?

246
00:14:28,055 --> 00:14:30,016
-It's not like that.
-So...

247
00:14:30,516 --> 00:14:32,727
Why do you get to just waltz in?

248
00:14:33,227 --> 00:14:34,937
Why? Tell me!

249
00:14:35,021 --> 00:14:36,272
Stop it.

250
00:14:36,355 --> 00:14:37,440
What?

251
00:14:38,524 --> 00:14:40,526
Am I the one who's out of line?

252
00:14:51,495 --> 00:14:53,080
I'm sorry.

253
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,002
I really had no intentions of

254
00:14:58,878 --> 00:15:00,796
doing anything with Tokiwa.

255
00:15:02,506 --> 00:15:03,507
I was just...

256
00:15:04,258 --> 00:15:05,676
just happy.

257
00:15:06,886 --> 00:15:09,472
It's been a really long time
since I've made a friend.

258
00:15:10,973 --> 00:15:11,974
So...

259
00:15:12,767 --> 00:15:14,227
I got carried away.

260
00:15:15,937 --> 00:15:18,064
I forgot about what kind of person I am.

261
00:15:18,147 --> 00:15:19,982
[♪ gentle music playing]

262
00:15:20,566 --> 00:15:21,692
I forgot

263
00:15:22,401 --> 00:15:24,820
that I'm just a ghost
who causes trouble for people.

264
00:15:26,322 --> 00:15:27,490
A ghost?

265
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:32,286
I will make sure it never happens again.

266
00:15:33,371 --> 00:15:34,413
Not ever.

267
00:15:35,831 --> 00:15:37,083
I swear.

268
00:15:48,302 --> 00:15:49,303
Hey.

269
00:15:52,848 --> 00:15:54,892
We've been together for a whole year.

270
00:15:55,434 --> 00:15:56,477
So...

271
00:15:57,186 --> 00:15:59,522
why do you still have your walls up?

272
00:16:00,564 --> 00:16:01,774
Then,

273
00:16:02,692 --> 00:16:06,904
have you tried
to tear down those walls for me?

274
00:16:11,742 --> 00:16:14,537
You're empty, Koji.

275
00:16:21,752 --> 00:16:25,673
[Takao] Look what you did! Once again,
you got involved and hurt people!

276
00:16:26,173 --> 00:16:30,136
I haven't learned anything, after all.
Just repeating the same mistakes.

277
00:16:30,219 --> 00:16:31,721
Kasuga!

278
00:16:34,473 --> 00:16:35,599
I'm sorry about that.

279
00:16:37,059 --> 00:16:38,102
Don't be.

280
00:16:39,437 --> 00:16:42,356
I shouldn't have gone to your house.

281
00:16:44,608 --> 00:16:46,527
It's not your fault, Kasuga.

282
00:16:53,576 --> 00:16:55,328
At the end of the day,

283
00:16:56,579 --> 00:16:57,913
I'm empty, too.

284
00:16:59,874 --> 00:17:01,250
I guess...

285
00:17:01,876 --> 00:17:03,711
I was trying too hard, you know?

286
00:17:06,005 --> 00:17:08,090
Being with Koji and those guys...

287
00:17:08,924 --> 00:17:11,302
It doesn't mean I can become like them.

288
00:17:15,848 --> 00:17:16,849
The thing is...

289
00:17:17,641 --> 00:17:19,101
I've never told anyone.

290
00:17:21,020 --> 00:17:22,646
That I liked books.

291
00:17:23,939 --> 00:17:24,982
Why not?

292
00:17:28,611 --> 00:17:31,530
Because they'll freak out, for sure.

293
00:17:32,114 --> 00:17:34,033
A room filled with books like that?

294
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:35,701
It's weird.

295
00:17:35,785 --> 00:17:37,161
It's not weird at all!

296
00:17:39,372 --> 00:17:40,498
I...

297
00:17:41,374 --> 00:17:42,500
I think...

298
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:44,210
[♪ gentle music playing]

299
00:17:44,293 --> 00:17:45,878
I honestly think...

300
00:17:46,837 --> 00:17:48,839
you're incredible, Tokiwa.

301
00:17:50,758 --> 00:17:51,801
So...

302
00:17:53,761 --> 00:17:55,179
So, I...

303
00:17:58,057 --> 00:17:59,433
I want to read it.

304
00:17:59,934 --> 00:18:01,644
The novel you wrote.

305
00:18:07,024 --> 00:18:08,192
Ah.

306
00:18:09,068 --> 00:18:10,277
I'm sorry.

307
00:18:10,361 --> 00:18:11,696
I did it again...

308
00:18:14,031 --> 00:18:15,032
Okay.

309
00:18:16,701 --> 00:18:18,035
Read it.

310
00:18:18,744 --> 00:18:19,995
I want you to read it.

311
00:18:22,498 --> 00:18:25,668
I want you to read that notebook, Kasuga.
STYLE
::cue()

312
00:18:30,131 --> 00:18:32,967
[muffled singing]

313
00:18:37,221 --> 00:18:39,598
Why are we in a karaoke box?

314
00:18:42,017 --> 00:18:44,437
I can't risk having someone see us.

315
00:18:47,398 --> 00:18:48,441
Let me read it.

316
00:18:49,734 --> 00:18:50,776
Not yet!

317
00:18:52,778 --> 00:18:56,991
I mean, I still only have the synopsis.

318
00:18:57,074 --> 00:18:59,577
Like, it's just a rough outline.

319
00:19:07,084 --> 00:19:08,294
Nevermind.

320
00:19:10,963 --> 00:19:13,048
Give me...

321
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,384
your honest opinion.

322
00:19:17,678 --> 00:19:18,804
Sure.

323
00:19:23,058 --> 00:19:25,603
PLOT

324
00:19:26,228 --> 00:19:29,940
POTENTIAL TITLE
THE GHOST MURDER CASE (TENTATIVE)

325
00:19:30,024 --> 00:19:31,275
Ghost...

326
00:19:38,491 --> 00:19:40,534
SCENE: A VILLAGE IN THE MOUNTAINS

327
00:19:43,954 --> 00:19:46,165
GHOST SIGHTINGS AT A MANOR
WHERE THE STORY BEGINS

328
00:19:46,248 --> 00:19:48,626
PROTAGONIST
A HIGH SCHOOL BOY STUCK IN THE VILLAGE

329
00:19:48,709 --> 00:19:53,923
BEST HITS OF 2001

330
00:19:54,006 --> 00:19:55,591
[♪ eerie music playing]

331
00:19:55,674 --> 00:20:00,471
[Aya] I'll just live on here forever,
feeling like I'm dead.

332
00:20:01,013 --> 00:20:02,598
That's what I thought.

333
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,269
That's when the incident happened.

334
00:20:08,604 --> 00:20:11,899
Several people vanished into thin air.

335
00:20:13,734 --> 00:20:18,239
Everyone rumored
that it was the ghost's doing.

336
00:20:18,781 --> 00:20:19,782
But...

337
00:20:20,282 --> 00:20:22,451
That's not a ghost.

338
00:20:24,537 --> 00:20:27,915
I have to discover the identity.

339
00:20:27,998 --> 00:20:29,750
[wind howling]

340
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:34,171
Who is behind this incident?

341
00:20:39,677 --> 00:20:42,096
I have to figure it out...

342
00:20:46,350 --> 00:20:48,352
to put an end to living like a ghost.

343
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:12,209
[♪ music swells]

344
00:21:16,046 --> 00:21:17,381
[♪ music fades]
STYLE
::cue()

345
00:21:25,431 --> 00:21:27,182
Sorry, forget it!

346
00:21:27,808 --> 00:21:28,851
Tokiwa...

347
00:21:30,269 --> 00:21:31,437
This is amazing!

348
00:21:34,690 --> 00:21:36,984
Surrounded by mountains,

349
00:21:37,651 --> 00:21:38,944
stuck with nowhere to go,

350
00:21:39,612 --> 00:21:40,863
nothing to do...

351
00:21:42,114 --> 00:21:43,741
I know this protagonist.

352
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,785
He's the same as me!

353
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:51,665
But he takes on the challenge
of solving this case.

354
00:21:52,625 --> 00:21:54,376
No one could come up with this.

355
00:21:55,085 --> 00:21:56,462
It really is amazing!

356
00:21:57,796 --> 00:21:59,256
It's fascinating!

357
00:21:59,757 --> 00:22:00,966
I can't wait to read it!

358
00:22:01,467 --> 00:22:02,968
Please write it!

359
00:22:03,052 --> 00:22:04,929
[♪ gentle music playing]

360
00:22:08,515 --> 00:22:09,600
Thank you.

361
00:22:10,267 --> 00:22:12,645
I'll try writing it!

362
00:22:13,395 --> 00:22:14,396
Yeah.

363
00:22:18,692 --> 00:22:20,903
There's no time to waste!

364
00:22:20,986 --> 00:22:22,738
I have to start writing, fast!

365
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:25,240
I already thought of the first scene.

366
00:22:25,324 --> 00:22:28,160
It's the sight of the people
who went missing.

367
00:22:28,243 --> 00:22:30,996
[chuckles] That sounds great.
It's so exciting.

368
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:34,458
If you don't mind,
would you read it as I go?

369
00:22:34,541 --> 00:22:35,542
Are you sure?

370
00:22:35,626 --> 00:22:37,252
-Yes.
-[chuckles]

371
00:22:40,547 --> 00:22:43,759
[Takao] It smells like... shampoo.

372
00:22:43,842 --> 00:22:46,053
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

373
00:22:51,225 --> 00:22:53,477
[♪ closing theme music playing]

374
00:22:53,560 --> 00:22:55,104
Kasuga?

375
00:22:57,022 --> 00:22:58,190
Saeki...

376
00:23:07,533 --> 00:23:09,410
[indistinct chatter]

377
00:23:10,828 --> 00:23:13,163
TO BE CONTINUED

378
00:23:48,032 --> 00:23:49,074
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

379
00:23:49,158 --> 00:23:52,828
[narrator] After an unexpected reunion
with Saeki, Kasuga flees once again.

380
00:23:52,911 --> 00:23:56,206
Still, he finally decides
to face his own shadows.

381
00:23:56,290 --> 00:23:58,459
Next, on episode ten,

382
00:23:58,542 --> 00:24:01,712
Kasuga's feelings for her begin to bloom.

383
00:24:01,795 --> 00:24:03,005
Translated by Yuka Kristi

